blog.name: weirdandwackypokefusions
blog.title: Well that's strange!
blog.description:
Welcome!  I create, using the all-mighty classic Microsoft XP Paint, my own pokemon fusions. All the sprites come from pokestadium and usually people on deviantart/ the xy/sun&moon sprite project. I don't own any of the sprite used, I just fuse them! 
REQUESTS ARE OPEN! Ask Box: 3/15.
PLEASE FEEL FREE TO DRAW MY FUSIONS!!  I absolutely love it when people draw them! There's no need to ask either! Just make sure you tag me so them I can see it!
I hope you enjoy my fusions!

summary: Sneaggy and Scravile Sneasel and Scraggy fusion and Scrafty and Weavile fusion Both are Dark/Fighting Type Ability: Shed...
caption:
Sneaggy and Scravile

Sneasel and Scraggy fusion and Scrafty and Weavile fusion

Both are Dark/Fighting Type

Ability: Shed Skin/Moxie

Hidden Ability: Intimidate

Sneaggy’s stats: HP - 60, Atk - 85, Def - 68, SpA - 30, SpD - 80, Spe - 76

Scravile’s stats: HP - 80, Atk - 125, Def - 100, SpA - 40, SpD - 105, Spe - 120

Sneaggy - The Masked Gangster Pokemon

Scravile - The Dangerous Gangster Pokemon

Sneaggy loves to bully other pokemon and steal their food and eggs. They are not afraid to start a fight for territory.  It usually lives in the cities where it will try to find someone worthy of its strength.

Scravile gather up other Scravile and Sneaggy to form gangs.  The gangs will usually surround a group of weak-looking pokemon and badly injure them for their food and other items that they may have. Serious fights can break out between Scravile to determine who the leader of their group is. It loves to rile up its prey through taunts.

Request for @cr-tist. I hope you like them.I don’t think I’ve done a scraggy and scrafty fusion yet so I decided to make them.  Also, Sneasel and Weavile just seem like obvious choices to fuse with them.  And thank you for the kind words.  They really made my day!

And strengths and weaknesses?  I suppose my greatest strength is that I’m kind.  I can’t say mean things to people because I don’t want to hurt anyone.  And my greatest weakness would probably have to be my fear of disappointment.  I don’t want to be a disappointment to anybody.

blog.name: pokegodsandmissingno
blog.title: P̵o̵K̸é̴G̸o̸D̷s̸ and Frightful Things to Come?
blog.description: There is a growing desire and expectation of humans here on Earth in making full contact with PoKéMoN who are still unknown. Back in 1995, when I saw my first UPM (Unindexed Pocket Monster), I found out very quickly that other people thought you were totally crazy if you said you saw such things. The world has changed quite a bit since then when I was a child. In fact, in late 1997, a poll taken in Kanto shows that for the first time ever, more than fifty percent of residents now believe in PokéGODS's. Since then, there have been polls that put the figure at over eighty percent or more.
